channel.title: [Delta 317] Two Errors While Compiling
channel.description:
I was adding a Korasi [u]designed for 317's on my server[/u], and I have everything compiled properly except for the [b]Special Attacks[/b]. I got this error while I was compiling:
[code]client.java:7400: specialAtk(boolean,int,int,int) in client cannot be applied to (boolean,int,int) specialAtk(true, 1872, 1224); ^ client.java:7959: specialAtkNPC(boolean,int,int,int) in client cannot be applied to (boolean,int,int) specialAtkNPC(true, 1872, 0x426); ^ 2 errors Finished! Press any key to continue . . .[/code] Could someone help me with why its doing this? It looks the same as all the other Special Attack codes. It doesn't work for player or NPC hits. Help me please.
[b]- Thanks, Excel4.[/b]

item.title: [Delta 317] Two Errors While Compiling
item.dc:creator: @No_Life2 No Life
item.description:
@No_Life2 wrote:

[quote=“excel4, post:1, topic:400734”]I was adding a Korasi designed for 317’s on my server, and I have everything compiled properly except for the Special Attacks. I got this error while I was compiling:

client.java:7400: specialAtk(boolean,int,int,int) in client cannot be applied to (boolean,int,int) specialAtk(true, 1872, 1224); ^ client.java:7959: specialAtkNPC(boolean,int,int,int) in client cannot be applied to (boolean,int,int) specialAtkNPC(true, 1872, 0x426); ^ 2 errors Finished! Press any key to continue . . .
Could someone help me with why its doing this? It looks the same as all the other Special Attack codes. It doesn’t work for player or NPC hits. Help me please.

- Thanks, Excel4.[/quote]

The specialAtk and specialAtkNPC methods require a boolean, int, int, and int parameter.

So…for example…you need to use those two methods like this: specialAtk(true, 1872, 1224, anotherNumber)

The method requires 3 ints and 1 boolean, not 2 ints and 1 boolean.

PM me if you need more detailed help.
